text = "[font_size=20][center][b]Statechart max auto transition round[/b][/center][/font_size]

In each step, statechart first handle transitions with parsed event 1 round, then transitions with null event for several round.  Transitions with null event is called \"eventless\", or  \"automatic\", as it runs automatically.

Normally after rounds, statechart will reach the status where active states have no automatic transitions to be pended, and will then stop. But endless loop may happens. Property \"MaxAutoTransitionRound\" makes sure that automatic transition round stops in certain iteration.

Also, you can set this property <=0 . This makes statechart ignores any automatic transition. It may save you some performance if you don't need this feature.

